    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-20T12:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-20T12:40:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1230.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-20T13:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Dominican Government will issue today decree for elections as follows: for
                    members of Electoral College, June 7 and 8; Electoral <pb facs="0348" n="232"
                        xml:id="pg_232"/> College to meet for work of electing President, Vice
                    President, Deputies and Senators, June 15. Newly elected Congress to assemble
                    June 25. Inauguration of the President, July 1, which is the date of the
                    expiration of Caceres term. This proclamation if complied with will preserve
                    constitutional government unbroken. I am assured by the Government that this
                    program meets constitutional requirements. Instruct if interrupted plans for
                    observation shall proceed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
